Procedure

# Mount two strain gages on the test specimen and check the gage resistance using a digital multimeter.

 

# Mount the specimen into the holding jaws of the uniaxial tensile test apparatus.

 

# Apply loading on the tensile test sample. Hold the load at various points and record the values of load (using the tensile test machine), axial strain, and transverse strain (using strain indicator and switching unit)

 

# Calculate the values of axial stress on the test specimen at each of the selected test loads.

 

# Plot the axial stress(load divided by initial area)  vs. axial strain (sa vs. ea)  to obtain modulus of elasticity.

 

# Plot axial strain versus transverse strain (absolute value) to obtain Poisson’s ratio (ν). ( |εt| vs. εa ). 

 

# Compare the experimental values of E and n to the published values for your specimen material.  Calculate the percent differences between the measured and published values.

 

# Identify sources of errors in your measurements.
